<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[722,1278,158,624]" box="[722,846,248,272]" pageId="4" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[722,846,248,272]" pageId="4" pageNumber="9">Comments</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[722,1278,158,624]" pageId="4" pageNumber="9">
The 
<typeStatus box="[778,874,280,304]" pageId="4" pageNumber="9">holotype</typeStatus>
male has only one palp left with a tegular apophysis as in 
<taxonomicName box="[977,1140,312,336]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Arctosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lacustris">
<emphasis box="[977,1140,312,336]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="9">Arctosa lacustris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The female has an intact epigyne with a broad median septum, as clearly shown in Koch’s figure 29 (
<bibRefCitation author="Koch L." box="[1076,1133,376,400]" journalOrPublisher="Verhandlungen der zoologisch-botanischen GesellschaFt in Wien" pageId="4" pageNumber="9" pagination="625 - 678" part="31" refString="Koch L. (1882): Zoologische Ergebnisse von excursionen auF den Balearen. II: Arachniden und MYriapoden. - Verhandlungen der zoologisch-botanischen GesellschaFt in Wien 31: 625 - 678" title="Zoologische Ergebnisse von excursionen auF den Balearen. II: Arachniden und MYriapoden" type="journal article" year="1882">1882</bibRefCitation>
), corresponding well with the epigyne of 
<taxonomicName box="[1015,1123,408,432]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Arctosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lacustris">
<emphasis box="[1015,1123,408,432]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="9">A. lacustris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(compare 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs. 11 - 23" captionStartId="5.[533,573,954,974]" captionTargetBox="[573,1299,172,953]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[552,1308,155,961]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs. 11 - 23. Figs. 11 - 12: Arctosa fulvolineata (Lucas, 1846). 11. Epigyne of Lycosa perspicax in KOCH (1882); 12. Epigyne of Arctosa fulvolineata in KNÜLLE (1959). Figs 13 - 16. Arctosa lacustris (Simon, 1876). 13. Male palp of Lycosa subhirsuta in KOCH (1882); 14. Male palp of Arctosa lacustris in KNÜLLE (1959); 15. Epigyne of Lycosa subhirsuta in KOCH (1882); 16. Epigyne of Arctosa lacustris in KNÜLLE (1959). Fig. 17. Epigyne of Lycosa conspersa in KOCH (1882). Fig. 18. Epigyne of Lycosa fraisei in KOCH (1882). Fig. 19. Epigyne of Lycosa insulana in KOCH (1882). Fig. 20. Epigyne of Lycosa simplex in KOCH (1882). Fig. 21. Male palp of Pardosa tenuipes in KOCH (1882). Figs 22 - 23. Thanatus vulgaris Simon, 1870. 22. Epigyne of Philodromus vegetus in KOCH (1882). 23. Epigyne of Thanatus vulgaris in SZITA &amp; SAMU (2000)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/556095/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="9">Figs 13, 15</figureCitation>
with 
<figureCitation box="[850,969,440,464]" captionStart="Figs. 11 - 23" captionStartId="5.[533,573,954,974]" captionTargetBox="[573,1299,172,953]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[552,1308,155,961]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs. 11 - 23. Figs. 11 - 12: Arctosa fulvolineata (Lucas, 1846). 11. Epigyne of Lycosa perspicax in KOCH (1882); 12. Epigyne of Arctosa fulvolineata in KNÜLLE (1959). Figs 13 - 16. Arctosa lacustris (Simon, 1876). 13. Male palp of Lycosa subhirsuta in KOCH (1882); 14. Male palp of Arctosa lacustris in KNÜLLE (1959); 15. Epigyne of Lycosa subhirsuta in KOCH (1882); 16. Epigyne of Arctosa lacustris in KNÜLLE (1959). Fig. 17. Epigyne of Lycosa conspersa in KOCH (1882). Fig. 18. Epigyne of Lycosa fraisei in KOCH (1882). Fig. 19. Epigyne of Lycosa insulana in KOCH (1882). Fig. 20. Epigyne of Lycosa simplex in KOCH (1882). Fig. 21. Male palp of Pardosa tenuipes in KOCH (1882). Figs 22 - 23. Thanatus vulgaris Simon, 1870. 22. Epigyne of Philodromus vegetus in KOCH (1882). 23. Epigyne of Thanatus vulgaris in SZITA &amp; SAMU (2000)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/556095/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="9">Figs 14, 16</figureCitation>
(taken from 
<bibRefCitation author="Knulle" box="[1109,1267,440,464]" journalOrPublisher="Archivio zoologico italiano, Napoli" pageId="4" pageNumber="9" pagination="251 - 270" part="45" refString="Knulle W. (1959): Uber italienische Arctosa - Arten (Araneae: LYcosidae). - Archivio zoologico italiano, Napoli 45: 251 - 270" title="Uber italienische Arctosa - Arten (Araneae: LYcosidae)" type="journal article" year="1959">KNÜLLE 1959</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[722,897,472,496]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Lycosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subhirsuta">
<emphasis box="[722,897,472,496]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="9">Lycosa subhirsuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its replacement name 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Alopecosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subhirsutella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="9">Alopecosa subhirsutella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
thus become junior synonyms of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Arctosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lacustris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="9">Arctosa lacustris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
